<H1 ALIGN=JUSTIFY><FONT FACE="Liberation Sans, sans-serif">Contextualizer</FONT></H1>
<P ALIGN=JUSTIFY><FONT FACE="Liberation Sans, sans-serif"><B>Contextualizer</B>
performs: </FONT>
</P>
<UL>
	<LI><P ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="margin-bottom: 0cm"><FONT FACE="Liberation Sans, sans-serif">monolingual
	single-word term context vector construction;</FONT></P>
	<LI><P ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="margin-bottom: 0cm"><FONT FACE="Liberation Sans, sans-serif">term
	context vector normalization.</FONT></P>
</UL>
<P ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="margin-bottom: 0cm"><BR>
</P>
<P ALIGN=JUSTIFY><FONT FACE="Liberation Sans, sans-serif">It requires
XMI files previously generated by the <B>Termer</B> as well as the
corpora processing results as the terminology. </FONT>
</P>
<H2 CLASS="western">Settings</H2>
<P ALIGN=JUSTIFY><FONT FACE="Liberation Sans, sans-serif"><B>Contextualizer</B>
requires the following parameters to be set: </FONT>
</P>
<UL>
	<LI><P ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="margin-bottom: 0cm"><FONT FACE="Liberation Sans, sans-serif"><I>Language</I>:
	the 2-letter code for the language of text files in the source
	directory; </FONT>
	</P>
	<LI><P ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="margin-bottom: 0cm"><FONT FACE="Liberation Sans, sans-serif"><I>Input
	Directory</I>: the source folder where reading the XMI files; </FONT>
	</P>
	<LI><P ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="margin-bottom: 0cm"><FONT FACE="Liberation Sans, sans-serif"><I>Terminology
	File</I>: the XMI file that hold the terminology; </FONT>
	</P>
	<LI><P ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="margin-bottom: 0cm"><FONT FACE="Liberation Sans, sans-serif"><I>File</I>:
	the output XMI file that stands for the contextual terminology; </FONT>
	</P>
	<LI><P ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="margin-bottom: 0cm"><FONT FACE="Liberation Sans, sans-serif"><I>Scope
	Size</I>: the context vector size given by the maximum number of
	terms before and after a given term, the window size can then be
	defined as twice the scope size plus one; </FONT>
	</P>
	<LI><P ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="margin-bottom: 0cm"><FONT FACE="Liberation Sans, sans-serif"><I>Association
	Rate</I>: the class name of the association rate ranging over these
	two values: </FONT>
	</P>
	<UL>
		<LI><P ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="margin-bottom: 0cm"><FONT FACE="Liberation Sans, sans-serif">eu.project.ttc.metrics.LogLikelihood
		for the log-likelihood measure;</FONT></P>
		<LI><P ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="margin-bottom: 0cm"><FONT FACE="Liberation Sans, sans-serif">eu.project.ttc.metrics.MutualInformation
		for the mutual information one.</FONT></P>
	</UL>
</UL>
